            "text": "AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service provided by Amazon Web Services. It allows developers to write and execute code without provisioning or managing servers. A Lambda function is a piece of code that performs a specific task or handles a specific API request. It can be written in various programming languages and is triggered by events, such as an API request."
